text:
Hey Charlie! Happy New year! Hope you've had a great start of the year. Just wanted to check in to see how you were going? 
All the best
Hi Nina, I’m very well thank you. I’ve started a few more projects and will send over the progress later today :)
More variation in the foliage and addional foliage is required for this piece, I was also told the focal point is a bit non existent at the moment so this is something I would like advice on please?

The final project is the group project, we still have another 2-3 months to work on it, I have worked on the whole environment such as terrain, texturing, scatter assets and lighting. I am working on implementing trees, addional assets and then moving on to the house. The other group members have been solely working on the house but are falling behind schedule.

As this project is in UE4 (completely new program for myself) optimisation has been a huge struggle, unlike Maya where you can just have millions of polygons in a scene UE4 struggles with this. Please note the trees are a work in progress so position, variation and colour isn't final. I have been working on a snow overlay similar to the terrains snow for the trees but it isn't working as intended atm.
